1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Be3 Bg7 7. f3 Nc6 8. Qd2
O-O 9. Bc4 Bd7 10. h4 Rc8 11. Bb3 Ne5 ({The modern treatment is} 11... h5) 12.
h5 Nc4 13. Bxc4 Rxc4 14. O-O-O Qa5 15. Nb3 Qa6 $2 ({After the relatively better
} 15... Qc7 {White would proceed with} 16. hxg6 fxg6 17. Bh6 Rf7 18. Bxg7 Rxg7
{The black rook is very passive, so White has a really easy game, e.g.} 19. g4
Be6 20. g5 Nd7 21. Nd5 Bxd5 22. Qxd5+ Kh8 23. Nd4) 16. e5 $6 {Becerra was
already looking for a knockout punch, but the execution was a bit off.} ({It
would be more logical to include} 16. hxg6 fxg6 {first, and then} 17. e5 {
looks very strong.} ({Alternatively} 17. Bh6 Be6 18. Bxg7 Kxg7 19. Qh6+ Kf7 20.
Kb1 {is just a nice advantage}) 17... dxe5 18. Nc5 Qd6 {because now White has}
19. Qe2 {attacking the rook with check.}) 16... Nxh5 $1 ({In case of} 16...
dxe5 {I think Julio had in mind to insert} 17. h6 Bh8 {before taking the game
to the endgame:} 18. Nc5 Qd6 19. Nxd7 (19. Qe2 Rd4 20. Bxd4 exd4 {is not that
clear.}) 19... Nxd7 20. Qxd6 exd6 21. Rxd6 {where Black\'s back rank problem
further aggravates his situation.}) 17. Bh6 Bxh6 $2 {After this lemon White is
back in the driver\'s seat.} ({Gelashvili missed a great chance here:} 17...
Bxe5 18. Rxh5 Bxc3 19. bxc3 Qa3+ 20. Kb1 Ra4 {and suddenly Black is
counterattacking.} 21. Qe3 (21. Nc1 Be6) 21... Re8 22. Rhh1 $2 Qxa2+ 23. Kc1
Bf5) 18. Qxh6 Rfc8 19. exd6 Rxc3 (19... exd6 20. Rxh5 gxh5 21. Rd5) 20. bxc3
Qxa2 21. Rxh5 $1 {A typical Dragon demolition.} gxh5 22. Qg5+ Kh8 23. dxe7 Qa4
24. Qf6+ Kg8 25. Qg5+ Kh8 26. Qf6+ Kg8 27. Rd5 h6 28. Qxh6 1-0
