1. d4 d6 2. Nf3 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 f5 5. O-O Nf6 6. c4 O-O 7. Nc3 Qe8 8. d5
Na6 9. Nd4 Bd7 10. b3 {A forgotten line. Theory favors 10.Rb1} c5 11. dxc6 bxc6
12. Bb2 Nc5 (12... e5 13. Nc2 Qe7 14. Qd2 Rfd8 15. Rad1 Be8 16. Na4) 13. e3 e5
14. Nde2 Qe7 15. Qc2 {White modest play is deceptive, as we\'re about to see.} (
15. b4 Nce4 16. Nxe4 fxe4 17. Nc3 Bg4 18. Qc2 d5 19. b5 {would be a sharper
choice.}) 15... a5 16. Rad1 e4 17. Ba3 Rfd8 $1 (17... Ng4 {looks attractive,
but White can meet the invasion to d3 with a timely exchange sac, e.g.} 18. Na4
Rfd8 (18... Ne5 19. Rxd6 Qxd6 20. Bxc5 Qd3 21. Qxd3 exd3 22. Nd4 $16) (18...
Nd3 19. Rxd3 exd3 20. Qxd3) 19. Nxc5 dxc5 20. Nc3 Ne5 21. Na4 Nd3 22. Rxd3) 18.
Na4 {White\'s main idea.} Nxa4 $1 {This temporary pawn sac helps Black to
maintain the balance.} 19. Bxd6 Qf7 20. bxa4 Be6 21. c5 Bxa2 22. Nd4 Bd5 23.
Rd2 {Possibly, a bit too slow.} ({One can look for improvements in lines such
as} 23. h3 Ne8 24. Bf4 h6 25. g4) 23... Ne8 24. Bf4 h6 25. h4 Qf6 26. Rfd1 g5
27. hxg5 hxg5 28. Bd6 Qf7 {I think Gelashvili became a bit ambitious here.} ({
He could have gone for} 28... Nxd6 29. cxd6 Rxd6 30. Qc5 Bf8 31. Nxc6 Rd7 {
which is about equal.}) 29. g4 $1 {This is the opening of a one-two punch that
will shatter Black\'s position to pieces.} Bxd4 30. Rxd4 Nxd6 31. cxd6 Rxd6 32.
Qc5 Rf6 ({If Tamaz only knew what was in store for him he would have gone for} 
32... Rd7 33. gxf5 Re8 34. Qxa5 Qxf5) {There it comes...} 33. Rxd5 $3 cxd5 34.
Rxd5 {It is very difficult to defend here as Black.} Rb8 35. gxf5 Rb1+ (35...
Rfb6 36. Bxe4 Qh5) 36. Bf1 Kh7 (36... Qh5 37. Rd8+ Kg7 38. Qe7+ Qf7 39. Qxe4
Rb4 40. Qe5 $18) 37. Qd4 Kh6 $2 (37... Rb4 38. Qe5 Qh5 39. Rd7+ Rf7 40. Rxf7+
Qxf7 41. Qxa5 Rb7 $14 {would be a good outcome for Black. Relatively speaking,
of course....}) 38. Rd7 Qf8 39. Qxe4 Rb4 $2 {The final blunder.} ({Only} 39...
Qb4 {was good enough to continue resisting, but Shankland only would have to
find} 40. Rd4 Qe1 41. Qh1+ Kg7 42. Qg2 Rxf5 43. Rd7+ Kg6 44. Qc6+ Rf6 45. Qe4+
{to put the game away.}) 40. Bc4 $18 Rxc4 41. Qxc4 Rxf5 42. Qc6+ 1-0
