1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 5. Bd3 Bc5 6. Nb3 Ba7 7. O-O Nc6 8.
Nc3 Nf6 9. Kh1 d6 10. Qe2 b5 11. a4 (11. f4 Qc7 12. Bd2 O-O 13. Rae1 Bb7 14.
Rf3) (11. Bg5 h6 12. Bd2 Bb7 13. f4 h5) 11... b4 12. Nb1 ({I thought the idea
was} 12. Nd1 O-O 13. Be3 Qc7 14. Bxa7 Qxa7 15. Ne3 Bb7 $11) 12... a5 $6 {Solid
move, but it surrenders the b5-square.} ({Instead, I\'d look at} 12... O-O 13.
Bxa6 (13. f4 e5) 13... Bxa6 14. Qxa6 Qc7 15. Qe2 d5 16. N1d2 Rac8 {with good
compensation.}) 13. f4 h5 14. Bb5 Bb7 15. N1d2 h4 16. Nf3 Nh5 $6 {Black\'s play
is one-dimensional, as he puts his hopes solely on the Ng3+ idea.} (16... h3
17. f5 e5 18. gxh3 Qc7 {with mutual chances.}) 17. Be3 Qf6 18. Ng5 $1 Ke7 19.
Bxc6 {Why hurry?} ({The natural developing move} 19. Rad1 {would leave
Goldenberg wondering what to do next, and he only had 4 minutes left on his
clock.} {The desperate} Qxb2 {is bound to fall to} 20. Bxa7 Rxa7 (20... Nxa7
21. Rxd6 {is crushing}) 21. f5 {e.g.} Nf6 22. fxe6 fxe6 23. Qf2 h3 24. gxh3 {
with Qb6 to follow}) 19... Bxc6 20. Nxa5 $2 {Too eager to cash his chips in
White allows  his opponent to start a dangerous attack.} ({It wasn\'t too late
for the prudent} 20. Bxa7 Rxa7 21. Qe3 Ra6 22. Rad1 {By the looks of it White
has to be winning here.}) 20... Ng3+ 21. hxg3 hxg3+ 22. Kg1 (22. Nh3 Bxe4 23.
Kg1 {trasnsposes}) 22... Bxe4 $1 {Goldenberg moves in for the kill.} ({He was
no longer interested in just getting his piece back.} 22... Bxe3+ 23. Qxe3 Rxa5
24. Rad1 $13) 23. Nh3 Rxh3 $5 ({Still,} 23... Bxe3+ 24. Qxe3 Qf5 25. Qxg3 Qxa5
{would give Black a great position without any risk.}) 24. gxh3 Qh4 25. Bxa7
Qxh3 26. Rf3 Rxa7 27. Nb3 Rc7 28. Nd4 Rc4 (28... Qh2+ 29. Qxh2 gxh2+ 30. Kxh2
Bxf3 31. Nxf3 Rxc2+ 32. Kg3 Rxb2 33. a5 b3 34. Ra3 Ra2 35. Rxb3 Rxa5 {has to
be drawn with reasonable play.}) 29. Rd1 Bxf3 30. Nxf3 Rxf4 31. a5 (31. Rd4 g5
$11) 31... Qh5 32. Nd4 Qd5 (32... Qh4 33. Nf3 Qh5) 33. c3 $4 ({Had he found} 
33. Qb5 $1 {Burke could have won this rollercoaster game.} Qe4 (33... Rxd4 34.
Qxd5 Rxd5 35. Rxd5 exd5 36. a6) (33... Qxb5 34. Nxb5 Rf5 35. Nd4 Rc5 36. a6 Kd7
37. Ra1 Rc8 38. a7 Ra8 39. Ra6 $18) 34. Qd3 Qa8 35. Nb5 d5 36. Qxg3 Qb8 37. Rd3
{etc.}) {Now, it\'s Black\'s turn.} 33... Rf2 $1 34. Qxf2 gxf2+ 35. Kxf2 bxc3 36.
bxc3 Kd7 37. Ra1 e5 38. Nf3 Qc5+ 39. Kg2 Qxc3 40. Ra2 e4 41. Ng1 Qb3 42. Re2
Qa4 43. Kf2 Qxa5 44. Rxe4 Qf5+ 45. Ke3 Qc5+ 46. Rd4 f5 47. Ne2 g5 48. Kd3 Qb5+
49. Kd2 f4 50. Nc3 Qb2+ 51. Kd3 Qf2 52. Rxd6+ Ke7 53. Rd4 Qf1+ 54. Ke4 Qe1+ 55.
Kd3 Kf7 56. Rd5 Kg6 57. Rd6+ Kh5 58. Nd5 Qe5 59. Nf6+ Kh4 60. Ne4 Qb5+ 61. Kd2
Kh3 62. Nf2+ Kg2 63. Nd3 Qa5+ 64. Kd1 Qa4+ 65. Kd2 Qa2+ 66. Kd1 Qa4+ 67. Kd2 g4
68. Ne1+ Kg3 69. Rd3+ f3 70. Nc2 Kf2 71. Ra3 Qxa3 72. Nxa3 g3 0-1
